tags.description: Fossil-rich beach below Sedbury Cliff, with a marshy and muddy approach from the footpath. Fossils are mostly c. 200 mya and fallen from the top of the eroded cliff, containing Jurassic ammonites, brachiopods and gravel with small crinoid fragments.
tags.name: Fossil Beach
